 |__| |__|_.__/\___/\_,_|\__|                        @{b}(c) GREMLiNS MAXsWARE@{ub}

 User Cfg contains all user setting  options in a door run from a menu and
 saves the hassle of setting up a MAXs menu with each setting option. Wow!

 This is a tiny update from Version 1.0 of User Cfg ('96).

@endnode
@node run " User Cfg v1.2 by Glen Martin of GREMLiNS BBS"
@{"°°" link grems}
  _____         _        _ _
 |_   _|_ _  __| |_ __ _| | |
  |   || ' \(_-<  _/ _` | | |
 |_____|_||_/__/\__\__,_|_|_|                        @{b}(c) GREMLiNS MAXsWARE@{ub}

 Firstly (if you already haven't) create a new directory called "gremlins"
 in your doors directory. Assign "gremlins" to your doors path in the user
 startup sequence, eg: "assign gremlins: doors:gremlins" assuming you have
 the doors path assigned also.

 Move the "User_Cfg" directory  into the "gremlins" dir & run the door via
 a BBS menu, using MAXs Function 34, eg: "gremlins:user_cfg/user_cfg".

 You will need to or may alter any of the files, eg: User_Cfg.bbs.

 Need help, any probs or msgs then @{"contact" link call} me. Too kind!

@endnode
